atDirectives.description:
Use the `@variant` directive to apply a Tailwind variant to styles in your CSS:
```css
@variant hover {
  .btn-custom {
    background-color: #1E40AF;
  }
}
```

Use the `@plugin` directive to include Tailwind CSS plugins directly in your CSS file:
```css
@plugin utilities;
```

The `@theme` directive allows you to access values from your Tailwind configuration file within your CSS:
```css
@theme {
  --color-primary: theme('colors.blue.500');
}
```

If you want to use `@apply` or `@variant` in the `<style>` block of a Vue or Svelte component, or within CSS modules, you will need to import your theme variables, custom utilities, and custom variants to make those values available in that context. You can do this using the `@reference` directive:
```css
@reference 'path/to/your/tailwind.css';
```
